Hey, Norma.

01:04.674 --> 01:06.175
Hi, honey.

01:08.245 --> 01:11.180
It was nice having
everyone over last night.

01:11.281 --> 01:13.682
I'm so glad Alex came.

01:15.018 --> 01:16.552
Wasn't it?

01:16.653 --> 01:20.723
Yeah. Yeah, it was.

01:20.824 --> 01:22.124
Hey, I'm... I'm... I'm gonna go stay

01:22.225 --> 01:24.160
up at the farm for a couple days.

01:24.261 --> 01:25.761
I need to get the barn finished.

01:25.862 --> 01:28.597
- Okay. That's fine.
- Um...

01:28.698 --> 01:31.700
But we still need to talk,
though, when I get back,

01:31.802 --> 01:33.702
about Norman...

01:33.804 --> 01:35.805
What we're gonna do.

01:37.908 --> 01:39.542
I know.

01:42.646 --> 01:50.653
♪ ♪

02:06.369 --> 02:07.970
How are you doing today, kiddo?

02:08.071 --> 02:11.574
Oh, I'm fine, yeah.

02:11.675 --> 02:13.909
I, uh, I...

02:14.010 --> 02:15.744
guess I should get down to the office

02:15.846 --> 02:18.714
now that Emma can only
work a few hours a week.

02:18.815 --> 02:21.717
Are you worried about her?

02:21.818 --> 02:23.018
Well, I've always worried about her.

02:23.119 --> 02:24.587
She's gonna die.

02:24.688 --> 02:26.155
I mean, I guess we all are,

02:26.256 --> 02:27.957
but it's just horrible
to think about, you know,

02:28.058 --> 02:30.092
and there's a lot of things
that are horrible to think about.

02:30.193 --> 02:32.895
It's a wonder everyone
hasn't lost their minds.

02:49.145 --> 02:52.915
What the hell is going on?

02:53.016 --> 02:54.950
I have no idea, Mother.

03:01.958 --> 03:04.860
What is happening here?

03:04.961 --> 03:06.095
Hey, keep off!

03:06.196 --> 03:09.131
What the hell are you doing, huh?

03:09.232 --> 03:11.734
Excuse me. What... There
must be some mistake.

03:11.835 --> 03:13.002
What is going on?

03:13.103 --> 03:15.804
We have orders to dig
a hole for a new pool.

03:15.906 --> 03:18.540
A pool?

03:18.642 --> 03:20.542
Really? A pool.

03:20.644 --> 03:21.911
Well, where are the plans?

03:22.012 --> 03:24.213
Mm. Bob Paris signed off on them.

03:24.314 --> 03:25.915
But I didn't... I haven't seen them yet.

03:26.016 --> 03:27.683
All I can tell you is
they've been authorized.

03:27.784 --> 03:29.018
Okay, but don't you think
I should see the plans?

03:29.119 --> 03:30.619
I mean, it is my pool.

03:30.720 --> 03:32.988
If you got any questions,
you got to call Bob Paris.

03:33.089 --> 03:34.556
Okay.

03:34.658 --> 03:36.191
What on Earth is going on?

03:36.293 --> 03:40.562
Um, they are digging a
hole for the new pool.

03:40.664 --> 03:42.898
Since when?

03:42.999 --> 03:45.801
Um, I just thought it
would be a great investment

03:45.902 --> 03:47.570
for... for the motel.

03:47.671 --> 03:49.571
Huh, well, that's
interesting, since you told me

03:49.673 --> 03:51.106
we didn't have the money
to buy down comforters.

03:51.207 --> 03:54.009
Norman, just be happy
you're getting a pool.

03:58.415 --> 04:01.150
Okey dokey. Well, I'll be in the office.

04:01.251 --> 04:04.520
And you should go put some clothes on.

04:04.621 --> 04:12.628
